<hgroup>
	<h1 aria-label="Forms - Inputs">Forms</h1>
	<h2 aria-hidden="true">Inputs</h2>
</hgroup>

<article aria-label="Forms documentation - inputs">
	<h2>Base Inputs</h2>
	<CardCode code={inputsCode} examplePosition="top"></CardCode>
</article>

<article aria-label="Forms documentation - selectbox">
	<h2>Selectbox</h2>
	<CardCode code={selectCode} examplePosition="top"></CardCode>

	<section>
		<h2>Custom Selectbox</h2>

		<p>
			Is a regular <code>select</code> element with additional features enabled by
			<code>appearance: base-select;</code>. It requires <code>button</code> element as direct child
			with <code>selectedcontent</code> element in it.
		</p>
		<h3>Available elements:</h3>
		<dl>
			<dt><code>select</code></dt>
			<dd>
				<p>is regular html form element with newly available styles applied to it.</p>
			</dd>
			<dt><code>option</code></dt>
			<dd>
				<p>represents value to be chosen in the select.</p>
			</dd>
			<dt><code>optgroup</code></dt>
			<dd>
				<p>
					wraps several options into a group. If <code>legend</code> is present inside, it will be used
					as label for the group
				</p>
			</dd>
			<dt><code>legend</code></dt>
			<dd>
				<p>To be used inside <code>optgroup</code>. It will be used as label for the group.</p>
			</dd>
			<dt><code>svg</code></dt>
			<dd>
				<p>
					Any element can be used inside <code>option</code> of a custom select. However if
					<code>svg</code> is used. It gets special treatment. It is scaled to an icon preceding any
					text of the <code>option</code>.
				</p>
			</dd>
		</dl>

		<h3>Simple example</h3>
		<CardCode code={selectCustomCode} examplePosition="top"></CardCode>

		<h3>Advanced example</h3>
		<CardCode code={selectCustomAdvancedCode} examplePosition="top"></CardCode>
	</section>
</article>

<article aria-label="Forms documentation - non-text inputs">
	<h2>Non-text Inputs</h2>
	<CardCode code={otherInputsCode} examplePosition="top"></CardCode>
</article>

